,{"section":5,"text":"He has tenderness in the knee area, and the physical exam shows a swollen and prominent tibial tubercle.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.060744,0.11698,0.1147,0.12079,0.10367,0.096241,0.091749,0.078906,0.06594,0.056291,0.050672,0.043308],"unified_progress":[0.067994,0.10484,0.10358,0.10513,0.1013,0.095745,0.088731,0.085445,0.080179,0.066134,0.055744,0.045179]},{"section":6,"text":"Hmm, the tibial tubercle is the bony bump on the shinbone, right?","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.34595,0.14427,0.078503,0.057317,0.065121,0.061946,0.052304,0.055785,0.049254,0.034821,0.035251,0.019485],"unified_progress":[0.23024,0.093383,0.071663,0.06771,0.078694,0.073121,0.08377,0.076152,0.070387,0.056084,0.051038,0.04776]},{"section":7,"text":"So if it's swollen and prominent, maybe it's inflamed or something is pressing against it.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.10353,0.11118,0.11063,0.10646,0.099331,0.092084,0.08589,0.075557,0.067598,0.058879,0.048627,0.040242],"unified_progress":[0.073693,0.098929,0.07169,0.10146,0.10224,0.10218,0.093807,0.08942,0.082541,0.074409,0.063076,0.046547]},{"section":8,"text":"The radiographs (X-rays) came back unremarkable, which means there's no fracture or other obvious issues like that.","dimension":5,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041199,0.074893,0.097499,0.10967,0.10805,0.10593,0.10206,0.094168,0.083646,0.074952,0.064311,0.043625],"unified_progress":[0.038329,0.072744,0.087957,0.097722,0.10545,0.10061,0.099797,0.096892,0.094708,0.08752,0.069976,0.048298]},{"section":9,"text":"So it's probably not a break or a stress fracture, which are common in athletes.","dimension":5,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032848,0.059299,0.080548,0.090406,0.094665,0.098541,0.099901,0.10266,0.10029,0.098156,0.08599,0.056703],"unified_progress":[0.033447,0.061359,0.077087,0.086022,0.09599,0.097165,0.10161,0.10569,0.1026,0.10399,0.082557,0.052482]},{"section":10,"text":"Now, thinking about the tibial tubercle, I remember that sometimes the patellar tendon can get inflamed.","dimension":11,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042188,0.072631,0.080813,0.090342,0.093172,0.095328,0.10165,0.09595,0.092453,0.091479,0.0791,0.064894],"unified_progress":[0.036747,0.067888,0.082968,0.095774,0.098005,0.09947,0.10349,0.097253,0.094353,0.089667,0.075603,0.058784]},{"section":11,"text":"The patellar tendon connects the kneecap (patella) to the shinbone (tibia).","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029139,0.054292,0.07296,0.086189,0.10015,0.10741,0.11037,0.11105,0.10514,0.090101,0.072432,0.060769],"unified_progress":[0.033416,0.062879,0.08349,0.095839,0.10188,0.11375,0.10622,0.10165,0.094918,0.086005,0.067755,0.052192]},{"section":12,"text":"If it's inflamed, that's called patellar tendinitis.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031812,0.050064,0.068449,0.081913,0.09746,0.10565,0.1103,0.11274,0.10787,0.094382,0.075889,0.063465],"unified_progress":[0.034157,0.060334,0.08217,0.096268,0.10141,0.11128,0.10733,0.10277,0.095861,0.087811,0.068905,0.051706]},{"section":13,"text":"The tenderness and swelling around the tibial tubercle make sense because that's where the tendon attaches.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.044808,0.052949,0.068444,0.080964,0.092836,0.10027,0.10427,0.1056,0.1014,0.090829,0.08145,0.076187],"unified_progress":[0.043284,0.061655,0.078777,0.090786,0.096795,0.10303,0.10058,0.098809,0.09534,0.087318,0.076727,0.066899]},{"section":14,"text":"Another possibility could be Osgood-Schlatter's disease, which is an inflammation of the growth plate at the tibial tubercle.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.024988,0.048063,0.06817,0.082033,0.096955,0.10559,0.11052,0.11352,0.10947,0.096672,0.078726,0.06529],"unified_progress":[0.030455,0.0